The open-source components (host, emb-public) are released under the MIT License
and may be freely used, modified, and distributed under its terms.

The core engine (emb-core), including motion planning algorithms, flow control
algorithms, trajectory optimization, and related core functionality, is NOT open
source. It is distributed as pre-compiled binaries under a proprietary license.
Commercial use of the core engine requires a separate commercial license.

